#HELPS

0 BANDING~
The Banding skill is often used by those who work better in groups than
they do alone.  A player with Banding gains a +1 to hit and +1 damage bonus
for every PC member of the party he is in.  Players grouping with someone
with the Banding skill gain a to hit/ damage bonus equal to their skill
ranking.

Ie, Campaigners have Banding(1), all grouping with Campaigners get +1 to hit
and +1 to damage.  Younglings might have Banding(2), so people grouping with
a Youngling would gain +2 to hit and +2 damage.  
 
  See also: CAMPAIGNER, WARRIOR
~

0 CHANNEL~
CHANNEL
Syntax: channel <weave> <target>

Before you can channel a weave or talent, you have to practice it.  The
more you practice, the higher chance you have of success. Also, you must
have embraced or seized The One Power.

The <target> is optional.  Many weaves which need targets will use an
appropriate default target, especially during combat.

If the weave name is more than one word, then you must use quotes.
Example: weave 'clear poison' frag.  Quoting is optional for single-word
weaves. You can also abbreviate the weave name.

When you weave an offensive ability or talent, the victim usually gets a
saving throw. The effect of your weave is reduced or eliminated if the
victim makes the saving throw successfully.

** WARNING: Drawing more of the One Power than you can handle may
burn out your character or SLAY them outright.
 
  See also SCORE, IC_CHANNELING  
~

0 CHANNELING CHANNELER~
CHANNELING, CHANNELERS

The Wheel of Time turns, and Ages come and pass. The One Power (or Source)
is what drives the Wheel of Time. This Power is seperated into two equal
parts, the female Saidar and the male Saidin. Men and women who can use and
direct currents (also called flows) of this Power are called "channelers".
Most women channelers are known as Aes Sedai, who train in the White Tower.

However, back in the Age of Legends, an Age past and an Age yet to come, a
man by the name of Lews Therin (also called the Dragon) and 100 of his
companions journied into Shayol Ghul to seal the Dark One into a prison. As
a counterstroke, the Dark One tainted the male half of the Source, saidin.

This taint drove the male channelers insane, and they wreaked havoc on the
world in their madness. This was called the Breaking. This Breaking did
many different, horrible things to different places and people. Mountains
rose where there were once valleys. Part of a pacifist people were thrown
into a barren land. Ogier were forced away from their steddings, some to be
taken by the Longing and die.

Saidin is still tainted today, and male channelers are feared and hated,
still doomed to go mad and die. A faction of the Aes Sedai, one of seven, is
dedicated to finding every one of these channelers, and severing their
contact to the One Power permanently. These women call themselves of the Red
Ajah.

Saidin and saidar are supposedly to be handled in two seperate ways. Saidin
is almost like a torrent, and must be seized. Saidar is gentle, and it is
said you must embrace it, surrendering. Training in both is required to do
even the smallest thing.

  See Also: AES SEDAI, ASHAMAN, AJAH, SAIDIN, SAIDAR, WEAVE
~

