0 COMMUNICATE~
In the WoT mud system, there are many different options for communicating
with the other players in the world.  Each of these is detailed under its
own heading, listed here.
 
SAY, OSAY, TSAY, DIRSAY
TELL, REPLAY, GTELL, GDTELL, CLAN
GOSSIP, AUCTION, OOC, QUESTIONS/ ANSWERS
 
In order to nullify any channel, simply type the channel name with no
argument after it and you will turn it off.  To limit the amount of 'noise'
you receive further, try these commands.
 
Cursing and pathetic curse masks are not allowed and grounds for
being no-channelled.
 
See also DEAF, QUIET
~

0 COMPARE~
COMPARE
Syntax: compare <object-1> <object-2>
Syntax: compare <object>

COMPARE compares two objects in your inventory.  If both objects are weapons,
it will report the one with the better average damage.  If both objects are
armor, it will report the one with the better armor class.

COMPARE with one argument compares an object in your inventory to the object
you are currently wearing or wielding of the same type.

COMPARE doesn't consider any special modifiers of the objects.

  See also EQUIPMENT, GET.
~

