0 DAGGER WHIP MACE AXE SWORD SPEAR POLEARM EXOTIC~
In this gaming environment there are eight different varieties of melee
weapons.  Because of the different fighting techniques used in wielding
these weapons, they have varying learning curves, damage ratings, and attack
capabilities.  This means that some weapons will be easier to learn, others
will do greater damage, and others will penetrate certain armor types
quicker.  Your class also also play a part in these factors.  
 
The damage ratings of weapons is listed below, from  to most:
1) Dagger                     5) Axe
2) Whip                       6) Sword
3) Mace                       7) Exotic
4) Spear                      8) Polearm
 
Please keep in mind that if a weapon is two-handed, it may ignore these
rules of thumb.  Weapons flagged 'twohands' gain bonus' beyond this file.
 
See also BOW, ARROW.
~

0 DAMAGE~
Both characters and MOBs have a hit point statistic.  Combat is completed
when either the character or the MOB fall below 0 hit points, or if either
flees.  The damage inflicted by your weapon is dependent upon several
variables.  

Some weapons do more damage than others.  Daggers do the least amount of
damage of all types, while polearms tend to do the most.  

Weapons of higher levels tend to do more damage than their lower level
counterparts.  

The more damage you have suffered, the weaker your attacks will be.  

Damage messages are reported in terms of how much damage you do in
comparison to your opponent's current hit points.  Damage messages are
reported in increasing syntax.  Meaning the closer you get to killing your
opponent, messages may be lower case, upper case, or flanked with *** or
>>>.  

See also COMBAT, FLEE, WIMPY.  
~

