0 DROP GET GIVE PUT TAKE~
DROP, GET, GIVE, PUT
Syntax: drop <object>
Syntax: drop <amount> coins
Syntax: get  <object>
Syntax: get  <object> <container>
Syntax: give <object> <character>
Syntax: give <amount> coins <character>
Syntax: put  <object> <container>

DROP drops an object, or some coins, on the ground.

GET gets an object, either lying on the ground, or from a container, or even
from a corpse.  TAKE is a synonym for get.

GIVE gives an object, or some coins, to another character.

PUT puts an object into a container.

DROP, GET and PUT understand the object names 'ALL' for all objects and
'ALL.object' for all objects with the same name.

  See also INVENTORY.
~

54 ECHO GECHO PECHO~
ECHO, GECHO, PECHO
Syntax: echo <message>
Syntax: gecho <message>
Syntax: pecho <character> <message>

These commands all perform similar functions.  Echo sends the message to all
characters in the same room as the user, with no indication of who sent it. 
Gecho does the same for all players connected to the game, and pecho sends
the message to the player specified as the target.  Any higher-level Imm
will see a prompt in front of your message, informing him or her that it is
a echoed message.  

Using these commands to feign a specific character's action that is
inappropriate is grounds for demotion.  

See also WIZHELP.  
~

58 EDSKILL~
EDSKILL
Syntax: edskill <class> <skill/weave> <level>.

Edskill allows you a method online for adjusting the level of a skill or
weave for each class. Using edskill if you feel a skill is set too high
for a class or too low it can be adjusted at your leisure. Another benefit
is that you do not have to recompile and reboot to adjust skills and spells 
which allows you to be more flexible in the balancing your classes.
 
  See also WIZHELP.
~

0 EMBRACE~
When a woman reaches for the half of the One Power known as Saidar, it is
generally felt as surrendering oneself to the Power.  This embrace then
allows the woman to use and control the Power as she so wishes.  Not all
women can channel.  While most female channelers were taught the release
that allows a woman to channel, there are some who can touch the Power with
an inborn spark.  Those with the spark and learn use of the Power outside of
teaching are known as Wilders.  
 
