number of creation points.
~

-1 GATE~
GATE
Syntax: gate <target>

The gate spell is a powerful transportation magic that opens up a portal
between your character and another person or creature somewhere else in the
world.  This portal will transport you and any pet you might have, but not
other members of your group.  Monsters recieve a save against gate, and
monster or players more than 3 levels higher than you can not be gated to at
all.  God rooms, private rooms, and no recall rooms cannot be gated to, and
no recall rooms cannot be gated out of.  Finally, any god or hero is also
immune to gate, as well as in player who has no summon set.  Guild members
may not be gated to except by their fellow guild members.
~

-1 GHEALDAN, JEHANNAH~
GHEALDAN, JEHANNAHNA

Ghealdan is a small nation which lies between Amadicia and Altara.  Until
recently, it was a rather peaceful nation, possessing stable rule,
sufficient trade, and numerous towns and villages.  That all changed,
however, when the so-called Prophet of the Dragon Reborn decided to make
Ghealdan his home.  Four different rulers have taken power and died within
the last half year, with only Alliandre Maritha Kigarin holding the throne
by means of allowing the Prophet to remain in Ghealdan, and making no move
to push him out.  Riots are common in Ghealdan these days, mostly due to
crowds of Dragonsworn attacking those they feel do not show enough respect
to either the Prophet or the Dragon Reborn.

Jehannah, the capital city of Ghealdan, is a small city, possessing many
two- and three-story houses, but few palaces.  Numerous shops dot the
streets, and Alliandre rules from the Jheda Palace, trying to balance the
Prophet and a possible invasion from neighboring Amadicia.

The sigil of Ghealdan depicts three silver stars arranged one above and two
below.  The banner shows the Silver Stars on a field of red.  The current
ruler of Ghealdan is Alliandre Maritha Kigarin.

  See also COUNTRIES.
~

0 GLEEMEN GLEEMAN~
GLEEMEN

Entertainers that travel in trademark patchwork cloaks, gleemen are known
known widely as top-quality performers. Playing instruments, telling stories,
and doing stunts make up this entertainer's life. The highest quality of
these are taken sometimes as court bards for kings and queens themselves.
Most usually travel from city to city and village to village, getting their
pay from the audiences' donations.
~

-1 GOLD SILVER MONEY~
GOLD, SILVER, MONEY

The Wheel of Time economy is based on gold and silver coinage (and the lowly
copper, which you as an adventurer are far too proud to carry).  Gold coins
are worth 100 silver coins, but are also four times as heavy (25 to the
pound, as opposed to 100 to the pound for silver). Gems can be bought to
alleviate weight problems from jewellers, they charge a mere 10%
more than they are worth. 10 gems weigh one pound, and they can be worth
more than 100 gold pieces for the highest quality stones.  

See also BANK, WORTH, SCORE
~

0 GOSSIP~
Syntax: gossip <message>
 
GOSSIP is unlike the gossip lines found on most DIKU muds, on the WoT stock,
it is more of a rumor mill.  Rumor spreads on faster wings than fact, and
is often anonymous.  When spreading your message through the lands, it will
appear as such:

gossip the Children of the Light have invaded Murandy!
Rumor sweeps across the land: the Children of the Light have invaded Murandy!
 
Be weary, although anonymous, spreading rumors can have great impact upon
role-play.  There are even some guilds that can trace the rumor to its 
source!  So just like in life- be careful what you say and who you say it
to.
 
See also COMMUNICATE, OOC.
~

