-1 GUILD_AIEL AIEL_GUILD~
`yAiel`w

1) An appropriate description: A desc of at least four lines is required and
should not feature any statements of action.  This means things like "<Name>
watches you warily," etc.  Descs should only feature physical attributes
that can be seen by anyone.  How they react or what you might be doing at
the time should be left for actual rp.  

2) A personal profile/background/rp plan: What I'm looking for here is a
sense of who your character is and how they'll react to stimuli.  What are
their goals?  Do they have any quirks?  A word of advice: everyone wants to
rp the toughest fighter and the most respected and unique individual in the
world.  Most Aiel -will- be warriors, but you'll need to dig deeper than
their profession if you want to be guilded.  I want the personal details
that make this character tick.  I'm looking to build a guild with real human
beings.  Supermen and earthbound gods need not apply.  Oh, and try to give
some thought to who your parents were.  Players have a tendency to have
either dead parents or parents who were 'great warriors'.  Not gonna happen,
people.  Parents and family can provide some of the greatest rp
opportunities, so make them interesting and unique.  

3) Aiel nationality: This one's pretty obvious.  I'm not going to be
guilding any Sea Folk or Ogier and handing them a shoufa and veil.  Make
sure you're human and of Three-Fold Land descent.  

4) An extensive knowledge and rp test: This is just what it sounds like.  In
the beginning I'll be giving these tests myself.  It's my intent to make the
Aiel guild an example for the rest of the mud when it comes to rp, and in
order for that to happen I need to know that you can play an Aiel.  Aiel are
one of the most difficult races to play due to their specific cultural
practices and their sense of honor.  For the most part Aiel determined for
themselves when toh was owed and how much was required, so it is absolutely
vital I fill this guild with people who not only understand ji'e'toh
thoroughly, but are mature and responsible enough to accept the consequences
for their actions.  

5) An understanding that all things are ic: This is the tough one, and it's
because of this that I expect few members in the beginning.  Everything from
eq to levelling will be considered ic.  What this means is that no guilded
Aiel will ever be seen killing children in Caemlyn while wearing fish scales
for armor and wielding a sword from horseback.  All activity by Aiel will
take place in the Three-Fold Land and nowhere else until we reach a later
stage in the books.  The main problem with this is that t he 3FL is
incredibly small at the moment and ill-suited for levelling.  I'd considered
allowing guild members to level oocly in the wetlands, but I decided that
doing such would only endorse bad habits that I'd have to correct later. 
This does not mean that you cannot level at all if you're Aiel.  It just
means that once you're guilded you won't be allowed in the wetlands.  My
suggestion is that if you really want a guilded Aiel char for sanctioned rp,
you make an alt specifically for that purpose.  Any guilded Aiel found
levelling in the; wetlands or wearing wetlander eq wil l be removed from the
guild and stripped of all guild eq and skills.  
 
Continued in HELP AIEL2_GUILD
~

0 GUILD_AIEL2 AIEL_2GUILD~
