-1 GUILD_ASHA'MAN~
`RA`Ys`Nha'm`Ya`Rn`w

The Asha'man "Defender" in the old tongue, is an army whose foundation was
set by Rand al'Thor, the Dragon Reborn, when he announced amnesty for any
male who could channel or wished to learn.  The call went out, and a
surprising number of men answered.  Whether they come to flee the
persecution of the outside world, to find mastery over their tainted
ability, or to find peace among others of their kind, they now serve the
Dragon Reborn as his army against the shadow, and the coming Tarmon Gaidon. 
With the help of His M'hael, Mazrim Taim, Rand created a system which
mirrored the White Tower for his newly proclaimed Asha'man.  Men begin their
training as "Soldiers."  After they have reached an acceptable level of
mastery, a Soldier is promoted to "Dedicated."  Only after he has proven
