58 HEDIT~
The online help editor works much like any of the other building editors. To edit
an existing help, type "hedit <name of help>" (without the brackets). This will
place you inside the help editor and give you access to the various commands.
 
To create a new help, type "hedit create <new help keyword>" This will create
the new help entry, and place you in the help editor to edit the various fields.
 
The commands available from within the help editor are:
 
keyword <new keyword>  Lets you set the keyword of the help entry. The word that
                       is used when people read the help.
text                   Places you in the text editor so that you can write, or edit
                       the actual text of the help. (What's shown to the reader)
new <new keyword>      Creates a new help for editing.
level <level #>        Sets the minimum level needed to view this help entry.
commands               Displays a list of commands available.
delete                 Deletes the current help.
list                   Displays a listing of every help entry.
show                   Displays the current help entry fields.
 
When creating new help entries.  Please try to follow this syntax.
Help keywords should be capitalized.
When using multiple keywords for a single help, enclose each seperate word or phrase in quotes.
Example: the help "Aes Sedai" should be entered as a keyword of 'AES SEDAI' (including quotes)
Lastly, avoid using the following characters in keywords: commas, periods, dashes,
semi-colons or colons.
 
 
A note about levels.
  Immortal commands should have a level no less than 51.
  Help entries that you want to be read during character creation, need to have a 
  level value of 0.
 
~

