0 IC 'IN CHARACTER'~
IC stands for In Character, and is a way of being. In Robert Jordan's world,
people and things acted quite a bit differently than we do today. When you
are acting according to his world and not our own, that is considered "being
IC".
For example:
If you say "Greetings, how do you fare today?", that is usually IC.
If you say "Hey, wazzup?", that is OOC.

In this MUD, WoT: Tarmon Gai'don, characters are expected to be IC as
often as possible.  While we understand the need to level is integral to
character growth, certain concessions must be made.  If levelling, or
doing anything Out of Character, you MUST put OOC in your title or rdesc
or else your actions are open to IC interpretation and consequences.
Exceptions to this rule can be found under help Guild_Areas.
 
See also OOC, WHEEL OF TIME, RP, RDESC, GUILD_AREAS, IC_CHANNELING
~

0 IC_CHANNELING~
To keep a balance between the IC and the OOC demands of the mud, it is
important to prescribe WHAT and WHO discerns whether channeling is IC.  Most
of these rules can be found in various places on the mud, but they are laid
out here for simplicities sake.  
 
1) If you are involved in active RP and channel or emote that you channel,
you are responsible for this.
2) If you are leveling IC'ly and channel, you are responsible.
3) If you are leveling OOC'ly and channel, your channeling cannot be open
to IC interpretation (unless in a mandated IC ONLY area).
4) If you are an IC Sul'dam and channel, you must have something pertaining
to your damane in your rdesc or title.
5) If you are an IC Damane and channel, you must have something pertaining
to your sul'dam in your title, or suffer the IC consequences for being
unleashed.
6) If you are an IC Novice and channel, you had better the permission of an
Aes Sedai or Accepted, 'lest you find yourself sent to the Mistress of
Novices.
 
See also IC, GUILD_AREAS, RDESC.
~

