-1 ILLIAN~
Illian borders the two much smaller countries of Altara and Murandy.  During
the Whitecloak War, Illian assisted Altara in order to insure that Altara
remained a buffer zone between Illian and Amadicia.  Illian is a large
nation, and does much trade by sea, land, and river.  It is ruled by the
King, the Council of Nine, and the Assemblage.  Men in Illian wear long
coats with raised collars, and the current fashion is to wear beards which
leave the upper lip bare.  Women wear wide-brimmed hats held in place by
long scarves that are worn around the neck.  High ladies wear slippers
worked with silver and gold, and Lords wear boots fringed in these metals,
as well.

The city of Illian stands on a marsh at the edge of the Sea of Storms.
Illian needs no walls to keep out invaders, as the marsh effectively
prevents any land-borne invasion.  The marsh surrounding the city contains
many large tanneries on small islands, which produce the country's vast
output of finished leather.  From afar, the city appears to be made entirely
of palaces and towers, rising right out of the swamp.  Upon closer
inspection, however, one sees that the city is made up mostly of small
buildings.  The large Perfumed Quarter (so-called because of the odor of
hemp, pitch, and harbor air which permeates the air) surrounds the docks of
