0 MOVEMENT~
A player can potentially move in any of six directions, these being:
north, south, east, west, up, and down.  The direction the player can move
is dependent upon the room exits available.  For a list of the player's
current room exits, simply type "exits".  

Movement from room to room detracts from a player's Endurance.  When
reaching 0 Endurance, the player will find themselves unable to move.  

Different terrains have different movement costs; cities might be quickly
crossed, while mountain ranges exact a harsher toll.  

Sometimes there may be a hidden exit from a room, as if found behind a
bookcase or some brambles.  These hidden exits are found through use of the
Search skill or by dumb luck.  
~

