Murandy lies just south of Andor and north of Altara.  As in many other
countries, commoners respect their local nobles more than the King.  A sense
of nationhood is virtually nonexistent in Altara, and civil strife is
common.  Murandians are highly suspicious of Andorans, the result of many
long years of border disputes between the two nations.

Lugard, the capital city, is located in the heart of Murandy.  Filled with
shops and inns, it is the trade center for the entire nation.  The city
presents a rather unkempt appearance to foreigners, with tumble-down walls
criss-crossing the city.  Most of the streets are unpaved, and the houses,
despite their brightly tiled roofs, are generally coated in a fine layer of
dust.  Lugarders have a reputation for thievery and licentiousness.
Foreigners are considered fair game for con games and theft, so its best to
watch one's wallet when dealing with a Lugarder.

The sigil of Murandy is a red bull.  The banner consists of The Red Bull on
a field vertically striped blue and white; three blue and two white.  The
banner is fringed in blue when the sovereign is present, who happens to be
King Roedran, at the moment.

  See also COUNTRIES.

~

