-1 MYRDDRAAL~
Myrddraal (otherwise known as fades, neverborn, halfmen, shadowmen, lurks,
fetches and sundry other names) are one of the most dangerous races in the
world. Standing about the height of humans, Myrddraal are highly
intelligent, and very similar to humans.  Having sleekly-muscled bodies,
they move with the fluid grace and deadliness of snakes.  In addition, each
Myrddraal looks exactly like every other Myrddraal, with sleek black hair
(which covers only their heads) and pale white skin.  Possessing
lightning-quick speed, they are consummate swordsmen, and extremely deadly
foes.  In addition, they have the inborn ability to step into a patch of
shadow and appear suddenly in another patch of shadow far away.  Perhaps the
most disturbing difference between them and humans, however, is the fact
that where their eyes should be, there is only skin, yet, somehow, they can
see in darkest night or brightest day.  The eyeless gaze of a Myrdraal can
cause fear in all but the most stalwart of opponents.

The only known weakness of Myrddraal is their fear of running water.  They
will go days out of their way to avoid crossing any type of stream or river.
Other noticeable traits include their telltale cloaks, which will not stir
or rustle in even the strongest of gales.  Instead, they hang straight from
the Myrddraal's body and never move.  Also, Myrddraal appear only as shadowy
mists when seen in mirrors.  Myrddraal blades are poisonous, and crafted by
shadow-forgers near the entrance to the Pit of Doom.  These blades are
tempered in the inky streams of Shayol Ghul and seasoned with the souls of
human prisoners.  Due to the nature of the weapons, the demand usually far
exceeds the supply.

Myrddraal are often put in command of groups of Trollocs, and, other than
Dreadlords and the Forsaken, are the only creatures able to control the
savage instincts of Trollocs.  They accomplish this largely through the use
of their eyeless gaze, inspiring enough fear in their soldiers to impose
some semblance of order and discipline.  In addition, some Myrddraal find it
necessary to link with their Trollocs, taking control of their minds and
wills in order to create a well-disciplined and highly effective fighting
force.  However, if the Myrddraal in control of those Trollocs in killed,
all the Trollocs sharing its link die with it.

  See also HUMANS, TROLLOCS, OGIER, SHADOWSPAWN.
~

-1 NAME~
NAMES
 
"A rose by any other name smells just as sweet."- W. Shakespeare.
 
Like most of what Shakespeare wrote, while this may be a 
pleasant sentiment, for our purposes it's just damn wrong.
Names, especially in a text environment, are the very first 
step in creating and maintaining an individual's roleplay.
Consider the following names:
     Draxxus
     Ludwem Unnerbulger
     Illethreal
     Brom
In reading all the names to yourself, already a few preconceptions
begin to kindle.  Draxxus is a warriors name.  Ludwem probably
spends alot of time reading books and cleaning ink off his 
fingertips.  Illethreal is a gaunt magical woman, while Brom is
a savage.
On this MUD, we are striving to maintain a Wheel of Time flavor. Players
are responsible for choosing names that are in synch with this
goal.  What does this mean?
If you pick names like Floyd or Larry, you will be asked to choose
a new name.  If you choose names like Allanon, Gandalf, Bilbo, or
Kirk, you will be asked to rename.  If you choose names like JKRTZ or
2hot4U, you will be asked to rename.
Common real life names are not acceptable.  Names of characters from
other books are not acceptable.  'Clever' names are not acceptable.
Thinking of naming your character after a character from the books?
Tsk. Tsk.  Please see HELP BOOK_CHARACTER.
Since the Immortal staff works hard to maintain a Role Play environment,
and since we take some abuse for our draconian allegiance to RP, we
ask that you help out by choosing a "proper" name.
If you like the sound of a name, try respelling it.  For example:
Brian = Breahan
Andrew = Androoh
Phil = Phael
Gary = Gayre
Jane = Jaine
Common tricks:
'AE' -- try replacing a single vowel with a combination of vowels.
The ubiquitous 'H' -- Chuck an 'H' in there somewhere, even if
it's a silent one.
An apostrophe -- Use this one sparingly.  "Ju'uan" for example.
Above all, be creative.  Harsh sounds = a harsh character.  Soft sounds
engender a soft character.  If you need help, please ask an Immortal
character for advice.
Council has the final say on character names.  If you feel an Immortal
asked you to change your name unfairly, please note exactly what
happened to Council.  Appeals will be considered, but be warned: We
hire Immortals that we trust.  If they say 'No', 9 times out of
10 it will remain no.
 
See also BOOK_CHARACTER, RP, IC.
~

