55 NOCHANNEL NOEMOTE NOSHOUT NOTELL~
Syntax: nochannel <character>
	noemote   <character>
	noshout   <character>
	notell    <character>

Noemote, noshout, and notell are used to muffle characters, by preventing 
them from emoting, shouting, and telling, respectively. Characters who are 
noshout'ed or no'telled will also not receive those forms of communication.

The nochannel command is similar, but more drastic. It prevents the victim
from using any of the channels (gossip, cgossip, Q/A, music) on the game.
Nochannels usually result from swearing or spamming or violating the
rules on public channels.
~

-1 NOTE BOARD MAIL~
The note system in WoT is based on various "Bulletin Boards". Notes are
written on a specific board, and only accesible within it.  There are
several boards that come standard with all WoT systems, these are;

General      -- Used for general discussions for any topic.
Ideas        -- Suggestions for improvement.
Announcment  -- Reserved for announcements from the implementors.
Bugs         -- For posting bugs, typos, errors, etc.
Personal     -- For personal messages between players.
Q/A          -- A Question and Answer forum.
Histories    -- Reserved for character histories only.
Roleplay     -- A story/poem/song board.

  There are also message boards for builders and immortals only.

 The system for reading, writing and managing messages is really very
simple. To do anything to a message, you must be in the board that
the message was posted on.  To change to a different board, use the command
"board" followed by either the new boards number, or name.  Once their,
these commands are available;

note write     -- Begins a new message.
note read (#)  -- Reads either the next unread note, or if a number is given,
                  then reads that note specifically.
note remove #  -- If you are the one who wrote this note, this command will
                  allow you to delete it.
note list      -- Displays all notes in the current board. Including those
                  allready read by you.
note clear     -- Clears (erases) a note in progress. If you lose link while
                  writing a note, you can use this command to erase it, or
                  simply finish your note.
note catchup   -- Sets all the notes on the current board as if you had
                  allready read them.


  This note system was originally written by Erwin Andreasen, and updated
by Gary McNickle for use with the Wheel of Time Mud system.
~

