0 OBJECT_FLAGS~
Here are a list of the current object flags and a brief explaination of
their uses: 
-glow: the object glows, and can be seen in a players inv even if Dark.
-humm: the object hums, uhm.... right.
-dark: the object cancels out light in the room.
-lock: no idea, will get back to you.
-evil: the object radiates Evil if detected.
-invis: the object is invisible and can only be detect by the One Power.
-weave: the object is part of a weave or flow and can be severed.
-nodrop: the object cannot be dropped from the player's inventory.
-bless: the object offers benefits against Shadowspawn.
-antigood: good aligned players cannot use this object.
-antievil: evil aligned players cannot use this object.
-antineutral: neutral aligned players cannot use this object.
-noremove: the object cannot be un-equipped unless uncursed.
-inventory: the object cannot be looted from a player.
-nopurge: the object cannot be balefired, junked, or donated.
-rotdeath: the object will rot away soon after a player is subbed.
-visdeath: this object cannot be seen unless carrier is dead/ subbed.
-nonmetal: the object is not metallic in nature.
-meltdrop: the object will melt away if it leaves a player's inventory.
-hadtimer: the object will fade away soon after it is created.
-sellextract: the object always sells at 100% of its value.
-burnproof: the object will not melt away under intense flame.
-nouncurse: Remove curse weaves will not affect "noremove" and "nodrop".
-guild_item: this object is a guild reward.
-quest_item: this object is a quest reward.
-neverbreak: this object will never take damage from combat.
-hidden: this object cannot be seen without 'search', 'observance', or
detection weaves.
-nocount: this object does not count towards a player's inventory max.
-nosave: this object will not log on with a player after they have quit.
-lodged: used in code, do not flag objects this.
 
