-1 OGIER~
Ogier are a peaceful and reclusive race.  Known throughout the known world
for their skills in stone-working, their primary love is the care of the
groves of trees within their Stedding.  These Stedding are places where the
One Power can neither be sensed nor channeled.  The Ogier relationship with
the Stedding is a close one, and is more fully explained in HELP STEDDING.

Not only do Ogier possess much longer life-spans than humans (oftentimes an
Ogier is not considered grown until well after the 100th year of his or her
life), they are also considerably larger.  With the men averaging 10 feet in
height or better, and the women only slightly shorter, they dwarf Trollocs
and other Shadowspawn.  Believing in taking their time to deliberate matters
thoroughly, Ogier are a deliberately slow race, and, consequently, regard
humans as overly hasty.

Some stories recount legends of Ogier fighting alongside humans in the
Trolloc Wars.  These stories report Ogier to be implacable and extremely
dangerous when angered, which perhaps explains the behavior of the
Deathwatch Ogier in Seanchan.  The Ogier of the Seanchan are implacable
fighters, grim in demeanor and resolute in purpose.  They make up a very
small percentage of the Deathwatch, but are the most prized by far.  Charged
with protecting the Empress with their lives, they carry out their duties
with zeal.  All told, they are strikingly different than their brothers and
sisters across the Aryth Ocean.

  See also HUMANS, MYRDDRAAL, TROLLOCS, STEDDING.
~

