-1 PKILL PKILLING PKILLER 'PLAYER KILLING' PSTEAL PSTEALING 'PLAYER STEALING'~
The art of Player Killing and Player Stealing are part of the roleplay of
any Jordan based Mud.  The world is based on conflict.  Still, to maintain a
level of fun for everyone, certain rules are set:

**PK is defined as attacking another player or channelling a weave of
malicious intent (ex, poison, weaken, sleep) upon them.  

1) You must have prior RP with the player you are about to enter battle
with.  This RP does not expire until one of the players is KILLED or
recreates.
2) You must be guilded to initiate a PK with another player.
3) You must be within 5 levels of your victim.
4) If you are going to join a PK already in progress, you must give some 
form oc IC warning prior.  Either by shouting a rallying cry, or directly
rp'ing parties involved.
5) Players in the middle of OOC levelling are still subject to RP for PK.  RP
takes precedence over whatever the character is doing OOC.  Keep in mind
that OOC'ly asking for a deferment of RP PK is possible, but at the
discretion of the player instigating the rp.
6) Players in the middle of guild tests, assignment, or quests cannot be
subject to PK or PK RP.
7) Players wishing to initiate a PK must be logged into the mud (not idle
or linkdead) and VISIBLE for five minutes prior to the attack.  It is every
