-1 SHIENAR, 'FAL DARA'~
Shienar lies northeast of Tar Valon, flanked by the Mountains of Dhoom
and the Spine of the Dragon.  Winter there is cold enough to freeze the
sap of trees, causing them to split and crack, while to the north, the
Blight lies in sweltering heat all year round.  The men of Shienar are
trained as warriors from birth, and spend their lives fighting to hold
the Blightborder.  Because of the continuing struggle for survival in
Shienar, each man measures his worth in honor gained, and not material
wealth.  Beauty, peace, and life are valued above all else, because the
warrior will fight until death.  Men wear their hair in a topknot,
shaving their heads around it.  Shienaran cavalry is considered the
finest heavy cavalry on the continent, as warriors in leather and metal
armor sit astride armored steeds, and carry long lances into battle.
Warriors are never without one or two longswords on their backs, and
they always carry a mace, axe, or sword at their belt.  Inside their
homes, there is a weapon within reach in every room.

Fal Dara is the capital city of Shienar, and it fully represents the
military character of the land.  Standing on a high hill, with the land
clearcut around it to prevent surprise attacks, Fal Dara is a fortress
in form and function.  All roofs are of shale to prevent attacks by
fire, and are sharply angled to prevent buildup of snow and ice.  Its
tower-studded wall surrounds a city full of shops, inns, and homes,
which in turn surround the keep.  A dry moat, lined with sharp spikes,
protects the inner part of the city, and a second defensive wall
surrounds the inner keep.  Other cities include Fal Moran, Mos Shirare,
Fal Sion, and Camron Caan.

The sigil of Shienar is a swooping black hawk.  A black swooping hawk on
a field of three blue and two white horizontal stripes graces the
banner.  The current ruler is King Easar, whose sign is a White Hart.

  See also COUNTRIES.

~

