-1 TARABON, TANCHICO~
Tarabon had been primarily a trading nation before all-out chaos broke loose
some short time ago.  It had formerly been a major source of fine rugs,
dyes, fireworks, and other luxuries, but that has changed now.  The King and
the Panarch rule Tarabon jointly from Tanchico, the capital city.  The King
is responsible for spending, the army, and overseeing the High Court, and is
protected by the King's Life Guard.  The Panarch, who is female, is
responsible for the collection of taxes, customs, and duties, and also
controls the Civil Watch and lower courts.  The Assembly of Lords is
responsible for the election of the King and Panarch.

Tanchico is one of the largest cities on the continent, and perhaps the
oldest.  Taraboners call themselves the Tree of Man, and claim descent from
rulers of the Age of Legends.  Indeed, there is a wall on display in the
Panarch's Palace which bears a depiction of animals no living man has ever
seen, and the skeletons of these animals are on display as well.  In
addition to these wonders, the Panarch's Palace contains a multitude of
sculptures, cuendillar figures, and even an angreal.  The Palace is open to
the public three days a month and on feast days.  The city of Tanchico is a
wonder in itself.  High, white-plastered palaces grace the hills of the
city, and gilded domes rise from paved streets.  In addition, ships usually
fill the Tanchico Bay, which lies at the mouth of the River Andahar.
Unfortunately, Tanchico has recently fallen into disrepair, as many of the
buildings have been neglected.  Homeless refugees fill the streets, and
thieves and cutthroats nearly rule the city.  While traveling the streets of
Tarabon, it is wise to bring along strong bodyguards.

