-1 TEAR~
Located well above the mouth of the River Erinin, Tear is nevertheless a
major trading nation.  Controlling all trade down the Erinin, Tear has grown
quite wealthy, and is the largest port on the Sea of Storms.  Tear is a
major producer of lamp oil, mostly derived from its expansive olive groves.
In addition, grain and fish are major commodities, and are traded up and
down the Erinin.  There are very few small towns, the result of heavy
taxation to prevent any town from growing large enough to rival Tear as a
trading center.  The Stone of Tear, which had never fallen until recently,
houses most of the High Lords, who control the country.  The Lords of the
Land are responsible for executing the decisions of the council of High
Lords.  The Stone of Tear was built sometime during or after the Breaking
using the One Power.  It houses Callandor, one of the most powerful
sa'angreal ever made.  In addition, the Stone houses one of the largest
collections of ter'angreal outside of cTar Valon.  However, channeling is
outlawed in Tear, even though Aes Sedai are allowed to stay in the country,
so long as they do not channel, that is.  Young girls are sent to Tar Valon
the day it is discovered that they can channel, and discouraged from
returning.

Outside of the massive Stone of Tear, the city is build on flat land.  The
inner city, with its paved streets, fine houses, and square-domed palaces,
surrounds the Stone.  Beyond the walls of the inner city, however, very few
of the streets are paved, and traveling the streets is extremely difficult.
Commoners in Tear are treated quite poorly by the nobles, and may not live
in the inner city unless they are servants of a lord or lady.  Those who
live outside the city live in conditions many would feel unfit even for
livestock.  Tairens, commoners and nobles alike, are notorious in their
hatred of Illianers.  The two countries are always willing to go to war
against each other, even though there has never been a decisive victory.

  See also ILLIAN, COUNTRIES.
~

