0 WEAPON_SPECIALS~
Included are a listing of the offered flags for weapons and a brief
description of each.  Also included is the Equipment Point cost for each, be
weary when creating your weapons.  
 
Special: Flaming (Cost 5 Equip Points)
A flaming weapon is a dangerous one, indeed.  Aside from offering a chance
to 'fireblind' your opponent, a flaming weapon can also destroy objects
flagged 'nonmetal' in your opponent's inventory, destroy their potions, and
does a little extra damage.
 
Special: Frost (Cost 3 Equip Points)
A dangerous flag at only 3 equipment points, a weapon that can frost
increases damage done, chills an opponent (sapping their strength), and like
flaming weapons, can destroy potions your opponent carries.
 
Special: Vampiric (Cost 3 Equip Points)
Quite an evil ability, a portion of the damage a player inflicts on an
opponent is absorbed by the player- as if leaching their life energy.
 
Special: Sharp (Cost 3 Equip Points)
The sharp flag gives a weapon the chance to double the amount of damage it
does, before Damage Bonus' are calculated.
 
Special: Twohands (Cost 1 Equip Point)
Weapons flagged 'twohands' will be allowed to have a higher MAX AVG damage
that those not flagged.  Builders can increase the MAX AVG damage of two-
handed weapons by 5.  This is not built into code, it must be manually done.
 
Special: Shocking (Cost 5 Equip Points)
Chars an opponents nonmetal equipment, electricutes their metal armor, screws
up their muscle coordination and attacks, extra damage... the shocking flag
has it all.
 
Special: Poison (Cost 3 Equip Points)
Weapons with the poison flag have the potential to envenom anyone hit by
them.  Not only does the poison continuously damage the player every tick,
but it prevents them from regaining HP, Ability, and Endurance back, even
while sleeping.
 
See also TYPE_WEAPON, BUILDING
~

0 WEAVE WEAVES~
When a channeler has embraced or has seized the True Source, then they
can weave the One Power into many different forms, depending on their skill
and power.  If more of the One Power is used, or it is used in a way more
difficult that the users skill, then drastic consequences can occur.  In
game terms this means that if a weave is attempted that is above your level
there is a chance that grows with each difference in level of a bad thing
occurring.  If channeling a weave that is beyond your power in any specific
sphere, there is a chance of bad things happening for each point missing,
which doubles for each additional sphere that is lacking.  These chances are
cumulative, so casting a spell that is above your level and that you are
lacking ability for is very foolish.  Some of the bad things that can happen
if you are foolish are small to moderate losses in ability, complete
stilling, and even death.  To see a list of weaves that details the levels
of spells, and required ability in each sphere, type CH LIST.  Note that
some weaves actually drain ability, and others use up endurance.  Ability
that is used up in this way slowly returns, but returns faster if you are
resting or sleeping.  If a weave is attempted that uses endurance, and you
do not have enough endurance available, then you also again have a chance of
a bad thing happening, more for every point lacking.
 
  See Also: ABILITY, SPHERES, CHANNELING
~

