51 rename_policy~
RENAME_POLICY
 
Renaming mortals is a tedious annoying duty.  But it's also one
of the most important.  As an Immortal, please talk to the mortal in
question first before simply announcing that they need to
choose a new name.  Help them work out a new name, realize what
was wrong with their prior name, and generally help them out.
Also, listen to them.  Someone who names their character something
that could go either way, may realize this and have a legitimate
RP reason for it.  If this is the case, and you feel that they have
a point, just drop a note to all immortals about it so the rest
of us don't jump on her.
Generally speaking, we are looking for fantasy names.  Not names
that are common to real life, or names from OTHER fantasy series.
If the name is -close- to a book name, just make sure that the
person isn't trying to Role Play the book character.  If they are,
direct them to HELP BOOK_CHARACTER.
What's acceptable:  Trust your gut on this.  There's no way we could
write a policy to cover every possible contingency.  Try to
be as lenient as possible without sacrificing the over-all
Role Play of the MUD.  The good of the MUD outweighs the desire
of the One (Thanks, Spock).
If there is a question, chat with your fellow Imms.  If you are the only
one on, just inform the character that they -may- be asked to rename
and explain why.  
If you need to rename someone, and for whatever reason you are
hesitant about it, blame Council.  Just tell that character that
a Council member asked them to change, and you are only the messenger.
We here at Council -love- being the bad guys.
If any character ever gives you lip, trans him to room 5 for a
few minutes until he cools off.  If he's still lippy, nochan him.
In either of these cases, note Council as to the particulars.
Council has the final say on names and name disputes. The buck
stops with us.
 
