0 "TINKERS TUATHAAN WAY OF THE LEAF "~
Tuatha'an are a travelling folk that live in a world of color, peace, and
song. Usually easily spotted by their almost neon clothes, "Tinkers" live in
colorful wagons and camps. The leader of the encampment is called Mahdi or
Seeker. They follow the Way of the Leaf, searching out the Song.

The Way of the Leaf is to accept what comes, and is a totally pacifist view.
Whether your belongings be stolen, your life be threatened, or family be
murdered, the Way dictates that violence is _never_ an option. Not even
wanting to touch a sword or other weapon, they live their lives usually in
peace. Children that grow up and choose not to follow the Way are called
"Lost Ones".

They search for "the Song". They have no idea what it sounds like or where to
find it, but they know that when it is found, true peace will be restored.
They travel and camp almost everywhere, but they tend to avoid cities and
villages since the people are suspiscious that they will steal their children
and possessions. They even travel across the Waste, although the Aiel shun
them as "Lost Ones".

Note: It is known by **VERY** few people ICly that the Aiel (an awfully
violent people) originally were Tuatha'an, and in the Breaking, were changed
and thrown into the Waste.

See also: AIEL
~

