0 'AGE OF LEGENDS'~
AGE OF LEGENDS

Before the Breaking of the World, there was a time when men and women
wielded the One Power side by side with no fear of any taint on
saidin.  This was a time when there were no wars, and even the word
"war" itself was lost and known only to scholars.  During this time, all
manner of wondrous feats and abilities were nothing out of the ordinary.
This time is known as the Age of Legends today.

Three thousand years have passed since the end of that Age and its origins
have been obscured and lost over time.  The information that is known
about the Age of Legends is scarce, and has been pieced together from
scattered highly fragmented records and must be studied carefully to gain
an even partial understanding of this amazing Age.

One thing seems certain, however. This Age was indeed a very lengthy and
flourishing period in the history of the world. Enormous cities such as
M'Jinn, Adanza, Mar Ruois, Paaran Disen, and Comelle were thriving jewels
of technology amidst the fields of crops and rich greenery which
surrounded them. The great research college of Collam Daan in the city of
V'saine drew knowledge seekers from all across the land to study and
discover new scientific wonders and the One Power.

Sho-wings filled the skies, and jo-cars raced along below carrying people
from city to city.  Crime was nearly unknown, with quick and certain
rehabilitation.  It was a time of unblemished peace and prosperity, with a
seemingly limitless array of possibilities and wonders of the universe
awaiting discovery.

It was not until a disastrous research project produced the Bore into
the Dark One's prison that the horrible truth about the Dark One
began to be suspected. During the Age of Legends, the Dark One was
unknown and his touch went unfelt. The Bore changed everything.
Though the Bore was not large enough to allow the Dark One to
escape, it was large enough to allow him to touch the world.  His touch
enhanced and manipulated mankind's baser emotional problems and
motivations.  A period of dark degeneration occurred which lasted
approximately one hundred years to one hundred and ten years after the
drilling of the Bore, and in several early resources is referred to as
'The Collapse'. The name is felt to be apt, as civilization itself nearly
collapsed, and the idyllic peace and order of the world in the Age of
Legends was shattered.

The War of the Shadow, or War of the Power as it is sometimes
known, arose when those loyal to the Dark One made an attempt to free
him completely and take control.  After ten bloody years of conflict, the
War of the Shadow ended after a male Aes Sedai, known as Lews
Therin  (also referred to as the Dragon), and his Hundred
Companions launched a planned attack on the Bore.  The Bore was
sealed safely at the cost of a great number of lives.  Within it were
trapped all the Forsaken (the most powerful dreadlords that served
the Dark One) that were present at the time.

Though the Bore was sealed and the followers of the Light prevailed,
the moment the Dark One was sealed away, a "backblast" tainted
saidin even as the Companions drew upon it. None know if this was a
deliberate action by the Dark One or the result of his efforts to
prevent the Bore from being sealed.  This tainting of the male half of
the One Power lead to the greatest cataclysm in recorded time, the
Breaking of the World.

Though civilization was maintained for a good many years after the
Sealing of the Bore, an inevitable decline into barbarism resulted.
Eventually every male Aes Sedai went horribly insane, and their
insanity literally changed the face of the world.  Over the course of only
a few hundred years, mountains were razed and new ones lifted.  Sea floor
upheaval flooded what was once dry land.  This great calamity effected all
until the death of the last male Aes Sedai.  The World was Broken, and
the Age of Legends ended.

  See also AES SEDAI.
~

