51 'AUTOQUEST RULES'~
AutoQuests can be implemented through the use of mob programs.
A few rules:
1) Try to run all AutoQuest ideas thru Phil first, so you don't make this
monstrosity that takes 4 months to write and then I shake my head.
2) One AutoQuest per area.
3) No AutoQuests in Guild Areas.
4) Rewards fall under Stock equipment rules, not Quest Equipment.
5) No inter-area AutoQuests.  They must be self-contained to the area.
6) Objects used in the AutoQuest must be flagged Rotdeath and Nosave.
 
Other rules to come as they are brought to light.
 
See also: BUILDING, QUESTS.
~

-1 'BAND OF THE RED HAND'~
(1) A legendary band of heroes (Shen an Calhar) from the Trolloc Wars
who died at the Battle of Aemon's Field, when Manetheren fell. (2) A
military formation which gathered to follow Mat Cauthon, and which is
currently shadowing the rebel Aes Sedai and their army with orders to
carry Egwene al'Vere to Rand al'Thor and safety, should she express a wish
to flee from her current situation, and also any other sisters who might
wish to join her.
~

-1 'CADIN'SOR (KAH-dihn-sohr)'~
The garb of the Aiel algai'd'siswai: coat and breeches in browns and
grays that fade into rock or shadow, along with soft, laced knee-high
boots.  In the Old Tongue, "working clothes," though this is of course, an
imprecise translation.
~

-1 'CHILDREN OF THE LIGHT'~
A society of strict aecetic beliefs, owing allegiance to no nation and
dedicated to the defeat of the Dark One and the destruction of all
Darkfriends.  Founded during the War of the Hundred Years to
proselytize against an increase in Darkfriends, they evolved during the
war into a completely military society.  Extremely rigid in beliefs, and
certain that only they know the truth and the right. Consider Aes Sedai
and any who support them to be Darkfriends.  Known disparingly as
Whitecloaks.  Thier sign is a golden sunburst on a field of white.

See also: Whitecloaks and Questioners.
~

-1 'COLD ROCKS HOLD'~
Cold Rocks Hold is the home of the Taardad Aiel, and is located inside a
huge stone butte somewhere in the Aiel Waste.  A huge fissure runs halfway
down the butte, and inside this fissure live the Aiel.  Houses line the
inside of the fissure, build directly onto and into the cold stone walls.
Families live and farm inside the fissure, raising crops such as corn and
tomatoes.

  See also AIEL.
~

0 'CRITICAL STRIKE'~
Knowledge of the body's key weak points allows someone with the critical
strike skill to find a spot on someone's body where an attack, whether by
fist or by weapon, causes great amounts of damage to the target.  
 
This is a group specific skill: Blademaster, Sam'Dain, Sovin Dore.
~

1 'DARK ONE'~
This is the most common name, used in every land, for Shai'tan: the source
of evil, antithesis of the Creator. Imprisoned by the Creator at the moment
of Creation in a prison in Shayol Ghul. An attempt to free him from this
prison brought about the War of the Shadow, the tainting of saidin, the
Breaking of the World, and the end to the Age of Legends.

See also NAMING THE DARK ONE, CHANNELING, AGE OF LEGENDS~

0 'DUAL WIELD'~
Dual wielding is a fighting technique found in various cultures of the
world.  While favored by Arafellins and the Aiel, the styles by which they
apply this skill vary.  When wielding two weapons, the number of attacks you
have will double, but you will be unable to use a shield or hold another
object in your hand.  Thus, you gain immense damage potential, but make up
for it in a loss of defense.  Two-handed weapons cannot be wielded using
this skill.  When wielding two weapons, the weight of your primary weapon
must exceed that of your secondary, or the lack of balance will throw the
