-1 ALTARA, 'EBOU DAR'~
ALTARA, EBOU DAR

Altara is a nation facing the Sea of Storms and flanked by both Amadicia and
Illian.  Had it not been for Illian's support during the Whitecloak War,
Altara would likely be under the control of Amadicia.  Indeed, Altara is
easy prey for outside attacks, due to the lack of unity within its borders.
The Queen, Tylin Quintara of House Mitsobar, has had great difficulty in
exerting influence over her people, and was in control of little more than a
one-hundred mile radius surrounding the capital, Ebou Dar.  Unfortunately,
what little power she has gained was swept aside in the recent Seanchan
invasion of Ebou Dar, and it remains to be seen whether the fragmentary
nobles of Altara can fend off the invaders.

Ebou Dar is a city of white buildings and palaces, along with some less
savory aspects.  The city of Ebou Dar straddles the River Eldar, with one
side containing the homes of the upper and middle class, as well as numerous
palaces with turnip-shaped domes.  Canals and roads criss-cross under
white-plastered buildings, and small shops often nestle up closely to large
palaces.  On the other side of the river, the dwellings of the lower class
sprawl out to form a part of the city known as the Rahad.  Duels are a
normal part of Altaran life, and Ebou Dar is no exception.  In the Rahad,
duels happen almost hourly.  However, many do not bother with the formality
of a duel, and simply stab their victim in the back.  On the other side of
the river, people are generally quite polite, and most do not look for
duels, but rather, accept them as they come along.

The sigil of Altara consists of two golden leopards, one above the other.
The banner shows the Golden Leopards on a field checked four-by-four in red
and blue, with red next to the staff on the topmost row.  Currently, the
Seanchan rule the city of Ebou Dar.

  See also ILLIAN, AMADICIA, COUNTRIES, SEANCHAN.
~

-1 ANDOR, CAEMLYN, WHITEBRIDGE, FOUR KINGS, TWO RIVERS~
Andor is by far the largest nation on the continent, as well as one of the
oldest.  Its royal line can trace its lineage back to before the time of
Artur Hawkwing, and the nation itself has been in existence since his death.
The ruler of Andor is always a Queen, and the Queen's eldest brother (or,
the First Prince, if she has no brother) is called the First Prince of the
Sword, and is responsible for the protection of the Queen and the command of
the armies.  The daughter of the Queen is always sent to the White Tower for
instruction (no matter whether she can channel or not), and all of the
Queens of Andor have had Aes Sedai advisors, a tradition which was started
at the very beginning of Andor's nationhood.  Andor has a robust economy
built upon its exports of grain, wool, tabac, precious metals, and ironwork.
Because of a decrease in population over the past few hundred years, much of
Andor is beyond the Queen's control.

Caemlyn is second only to Tar Valon in its beauty.  Resting on low hills in
the east of Andor, it boasts some of the finest Ogier stonework in the
world.  The Inner City glistens with beautiful white towers and domes, and
is surrounded by a huge, shining, white wall.  The New City, built by man
alone, is a glistening jewel in itself, and possesses many domed palaces and
fine houses.  An enormous fifty-foot wall, broken by large towers and arched
gates, encloses the New City, but houses cluster around the wall and
gradually spread outward from the city.  Caemlyn possesses an excellent
library, second only to the White Tower and Royal libraries of Tar Valon and
Cairhien.

Whitebridge is perhaps the second-best known town in Andor.  This is
partially due to the huge white bridge which spans the River Arinelle.  The
bridge is the only bridge south of Maradon in Saldaea which crosses the
Arinelle, and so, the town of Whitebridge thrives on trade.  The bridge is
believed to have been constructed during the Age of Legends, and it appears
to be made of fragile white glass.  However, the bridge cannot be scratched
by even the strongest of blows with a hammer, and it never becomes slick,
even when wet.  The town of Whitebridge sprung up around the stone-paved
square at the eastern foot of the bridge, and is home to many shops and
inns.  In addition, many ships stop to trade and to take on provisions in
the town.

Four Kings is a trading town on the Caemlyn Road between Whitebridge and
Caemlyn.  It acts as a trading hub between Caemlyn, Whitebridge, and
Murandy.  Consequently, most of the buildings in the town are inns and
stables.

The Two Rivers is one of the neglected parts of Andor.  Few of the local
inhabitants know that they are ruled by a Queen (or even part of Andor), and
still fewer care.  They are inordinately stubborn and independent, and have
been known to be extremely resilient in the face of hardships.  The majority
of the residents are farmers, producing the finest tabac and wool on the
continent.  Due to the seclusion of the Two Rivers, there are very few
merchants, and only a small number of inns.

The sigil of Andor is a rampant white lion.  The banner consits of the White
Lion on a field of red.  Rand al'Thor is the current ruler of Andor,
although he has promised to transfer rule to the rightful heir to the
throne, Elayne Trakand, upon her return to Caemlyn.

  See also COUNTRIES.
~

-1 ANGREAL~
ANGREAL

Remnants of the Age of Legends that allow anyone capable of channeling
to handle a greater amount of the One Power than is safe or even
possible unaided.  Some were made for use by women, others by men.  Rumors
of angreal usable by both men and women have never been confirmed.  Their
making is no longer known, and few are known to remain in existance.
 
