lost good friends due to my standing on these decisions.
But these stand.
 
Female Sei'Cair- Although we have never
SEEN a female wolfkin, it has never been said that
women cannot be attuned to the wolves.  It is the belief
of this mud that even the references of man to the wolves have
all been made as "mankind", which is to mean men and women.
So there can be male and female Sei'Cair.
 
Channelling Sie'Cair-  Okay, wolfkin and channellers
are two different animals, right?  Right.  And the
chances of becoming a channeler are reeeeallly small,
right?  And the chances of becoming a wolfkin are 
reeeeeaallly small, right?  So the chances of a wolfkin
channeler would be reeeeealllly reeeeaaaalllly small,
right?  Like 1 or 2 in 10k- 100k?  Fine.  It can
happen.  Once.  Usul Kentel.  The ONLY one we will
accept.  So no channeling wolfkin.
 
Ogier Hailene-  It is written that the Ogier are the most 
feared of the Empress' Deathwatch.  No Ogier have been
seen in the Hailene, and it would doubted that such
resources would be wasted taking back what the Oathbreaker's
have stolen.  Better they be spent protecting the Empress or
warding the Lesser Blight.  No Ogier Hailene.
 
Channelling Male Aiel- You may play a Channelling Male Aiel
if you wish, but you should be prepared that anytime after level 15
a member of Council may arbitrarily send you a pmote saying you decide
