0 ATTRIBUTES STRENGTH WISDOM INTELLIGENCE DEXTERITY CONSTITUTION~
ATTRIBUTES make up the statistical data of your character.  They are a
measure of who he/ she is or was, and are important in gameplay.  Here is a
list of you character's attributes, and a brief description as to how they
relate to the game.  
 
STRENGTH is a measure of the physical prowess your character posseses.
Characters with a higher strength hit harder and can carry heavier items.
 
INTELLIGENCE is a statistic that defines your knowledge into the world
at large and how you handle learning new things.  Characters with a
higher intelligence tend to learn quicker when practicing their skills.
 
WISDOM is different than intelligence as it relates to how perceptive
you are of the world around you and your judgement of the events  that
make up your life.  Characters with a high wisdom score gain more
practices per level than those with a lower score.
 
DEXTERITY is a measure of how quick and nimble your character is.  It
gauges how hard you are to hit in combat and how many items you can
hold at a single time.
 
CONSTITUTION is the stamina and vatality of your character.  It helps
in resistance to disease and poison, and higher constitution scores
grant a bonus to hit point rolls at each level.
 
 
  See also SCORE.
~

0 AUCTION~

Syntax

show 
Defaults to detail of last item bid on, or all if no bids. You can use any
of the following arguments with the show command.

	#       Show detail of the specified item
	detail  Show detail for all items (default is summary)
        bids    Show detail for all items currently bidding on
        winning Show detail for all items currently winning bids on
        losing  Show detail for all items currently losing bids on
        'name'  Show all auctions by a specific person (detail)
        all     Show summary of all auctions (default action)


sell <item> <opening amount>
Put an item up for auction
You can use any of the following arguments with the sell command.

        reserve Set the reserve price, if any
        open    Set the opening bid
        inc     Set the minimum bid increment
        commit  Commit the item to sale

Note that until you use the 'auction sell commit' command sequence, your
item will not go up for auction.  Once you commit to the auction, the item
is removed from your inventory and placed on the auction block.

Some examples;

  auction sell "uber sword" 1000
  --This will start the auction process for the item 'uber sword' and
  set the opening price (change with the auction sell open) to 1000 gold.

  auction inc 100
  --With your auction started now, this command will set the 'minimum bid
  increment' value to 100 gold.

  auction reserve 5000
  --This will set the minimum purchase price of your 'uber sword'. If no bids
  reach this minimum, the item will not be sold.

  auction commit
  --Will commit you to the sale of the 'uber sword' and place the auction on
  the block.


bid <#> <amt>
Use the bid command to place a bid on the item you want to buy. You must
include the auction # in your bid, and the amount of the bid must be higher
(by at least the auctions 'inc' value) than the last bid.

cancel/stop
Stop an auction process that you have begun, but not yet 'committed' to.

How to read the auction screen...

Here is an example output from the auction of a basic sword that can be
found anywhere in the mud.

//------------------------------------------------------------------------//
// 2   Rhuarc          a broad sword                             O:  1000 //
// -R- 0   No Winners yet                               M:  1000 H:     0 //
//------------------------------------------------------------------------//

 The '2' on the first line is the Auction ID#. This is the number you need
to bid on this item.  The next bit, "Rhuarc" is the name of the seller. "a
broad sword" is the short description of the item being sold.  'O: 1000' is
the 'Opening price', set to 1000 gold. The next line shows first, '-R-',
these are the flags for this item. The possible flags are QRG. These stand
for;

 Q == This item is a quest item
 R == This item has a reserve price
 G == You dont have enough gold on you to bid on this item.

  The "No Winners yet" will be replaced with the current highest bidders
  name.  "M: 1000" shows the minimum bid needed to bid on this item, and "H:
  0" shows the highest bid received so far.

 Using 'auction show detail' will give much more detail about the item in
 question.

Auction system written by Gary McNickle for the Wheel of Time Project
wotmud.tarmongaidon.org:5000
~

