-1 BACKSTAB~
BACKSTAB Syntax: backstab <target>

Backstab is the favored attack of thieves, murderers, and other rogues.  
Your character must be sneaking or hidden in order to backstab his prey.
It can be used with any weapon type, but is most effective with piercing
weapons.  A rogue may only backstab with a weapon of a light weight,
otherwise it becomes too unwieldly for such a precision strike.  Weapons
wielded with two hands cannot be used to backstab.  The damage inflicted by
a backstab is determined by the attacker's level, his weapon skill, his
backstab skill, and the power of his opponent.  Players who chose the
Assassin group also do excessive damage with backstab.  Only rogues may
learn to backstab.  

See also ROGUE.
~

