-1 BLIGHTWATCH_GUILD~
`NBli`YghtWa`Ntch`w

Rather than a "guild", the BlightWatch instead represents the full might of
the Borderlander armies acting in concert for mutual survival and honor. 
Food, supplies, horses, men, refugees..  All these and more are passed back
and forth between Saldaea, Arafel, Kandor, and Shienar.  Each of these lands
have their own laws and traditions, but all band together to keep the tides
of Shadowspawn from overrunning their homelands, and flowing south in a
unabating wave of carnage and destruction.  At the last Ingathering of the
Lances, Agelmar Jagad was anoited as the Warlord of the Blightwatch.  Since
that time, the following requirements have been posted at the gates of every
border-town.  

1)Male only: In the Borderlands, women are zealously protected by their men.
For example, in Shienar, women are safe no matter where they go or when. 
Even the fiery Saldaean women are kept from batle by their husbands.  

2) Level 15: We expect you to have some measure of skill with the sword
before joining the ranks.  

3) Borderlander only: Only men from Kandor, Shienar, Saldaea or Arafel
willbe allowed into the ranks.  On occasion, Southlanders who prove a
measure of honor and dedication sufficient to the task at hand may be
allowed to join, but this is by no means a certainty.  

4) Warrior and Rogues only: The Borderlands keep the Pact with the White
Tower, and any channelers will be sent to the Tower for Gentling.  

5) Tithe: We are not supported by the fat banks of the south.  We stand
alone.  As such, if a fellow member of the Blightwatch asks for assistance
of any kind (i.e. coin or combat) you must give it.  We have only ourselves
to rely upon.  

6) Your duties are to the Borderlands.  As such, members are expected to
stay in them.  If a journey south must be undertaken, permission must be
attained from the current Warlord.  Embarking without permission is grounds
for demotion or expulsion.  

7) No matter where you go, women must ALWAYS be protected and Shadowspawn
must always be put down.  There is never any excuse to break this rule.  To
break this rule is to dishonor all Borderlanders, and to earn yourself a
booting from the ranks.  

8) ROLEPLAY: This is, of course, the most important rule.  If you cannot;
roleplay the proper Borderlander attitude, you will not gain a position. ;
Any current Blightwatch member should be available to assist with roleplay
questions.  In addition, each individual country has their own quirks and
customs.  Your knowledge of these, but especially the customs of the
nationality you have chosen to play, will be tested both formally and
informally, at every opportunity.  

To apply, send an IC note to 'Blightwatch' and 'Agelmar', detailing your
history, personality, and reasons for joining.  Send this note by level 10,
so you may be watched and guided till level 15.  

May Peace Favor your Sword
 
-Agelmar Jagad
~

