0 BOW ARROW QUIVER LODGE DISLODGE~
Bows have been the preferred weapons of both hunters and assassins for a
number of years.  Being a long-range weapon, one is often hindered entering
combat wielding a bow, but can attack at a distance in relative safety.  
 
To use a bow, you must be wielding one, as well as wearing a quiver with
arrows left in it over your shoulder.  Most quivers only tell you the
maximum arrows they can hold (OBJprogs on the way to fix this slight),
so you will have to keep a tally upon how many you use from that total.
The command to shoot the bow is "fire", and your target MUST be in
an adjacent room to you, with no barriers (ie, doors) separating you.
 
You must not have anything in the 'held' wear position.

Once shot by an bow, you will find an arrow lodged into you.  To
remove the arrow, you will need to "dislodge" it.  Be careful, this is
often QUITE painful.
~

-1 BRAWL 'HAND TO HAND'~
BRAWL

Brawling is a skill commonly used by street-toughs or warriors who are
forced to fight unarmed.  Being skilled in brawl gives one a better attack
when fighting without a weapon than someone unpracticed in it.  

HAND TO HAND

A deadly form of unarmed combat.  Brought across the Waste by the Aiel, this
fighting style is making it's way among the people west of the Dragon Wall. 
It is a more advanced and civilized fighting style than brawling, but it is
also more difficult to master.  Being proficient in this art allows you
attempts at feats generally only accomplishable by those armed with weapons.
This includes parrying and disarming.  You become, in fact, a living weapon.

Players of the Sovin'Dore group gain what is called "Sha'mad Harad" (Thunder
Fist) when they reach the pinnacle of their attacks.  When each blow in a
combat round lands, the final hit does so for excessive damage and can stun
their opponent.  
 
Hand to Hand is a group specific skill: Sovin'Dore, Siswai'N'Dore
 
** This skill is undergoing heavy tweaking.
~

