51 BUILDING_RULES~
Thank you for choosing to help contribute to the Wheel of Time Mud-base.  In
this short chapter, we will cover a few of the basic rules we try to follow
for mud consistancy.

1)  Do NOT use the word "YOU" or any form of it in room descriptions.  Rooms
should not be interactive with players, they should be independant.

2)  Do not use colors in STOCK rooms, objects, or mobs. Yes, pretty flowers
would look nice in color- no, you still should not build in color.  Save
Color for QUEST and GUILD equipment.

3)  The length of a room description should be at least four lines.  Four
lines is not a lot- creative builders can easily fill a room with a dozen
lines.  Concentrate on all the sense, not just what players see- what scents
linger in the air?  What type of ambiance pervades the room?  What can be
seen to the north, south, east or west?

4)  Common Sense.  Use it- its your best tool aside your imagination.
Trollocs are not newbie mobs.  Biteme's should not be able to kill a Warder.
When building, consider the level of whatever you are working on compared to
how it would realistically hold up in real life.

5) Try to build each area with a sense of timelessness.  By this it
It is meant to avoid mentioning different facets of storyline
included in the running storyline (ie, book 1 +).  The reason
for this is, since this is a mud base, individual muds will be
able to declare their own time-frame.  Time based areas (ie, 
Dumai's Well, the Black Tower, Salidar, etc.) will be toggleable,
as will the Guilds, and might not be offered in the original
release but rather in supplemental downloads.

See also BUILDING, BUILDING_SUBMISSIONS, WEAR_, EQUIPMENT_POINTS
~

