0 BUY LIST SELL VALUE SHOP~
BUY, LIST, SELL, VALUE
Syntax: buy   <object>
Syntax: list
Syntax: sell  <object>
Syntax: value <object>

BUY buys an object from a shop keeper.
When multiple items of the same name are listed, type 'buy n.item', where n
is the position of the item in a list of that name.  So if there are two
swords, buy 2.sword will buy the second. If you want to buy multiples of
an item, use an * (buy 5*pie will buy 5 pies).  These can be combined into
(for example) buy 2*2.shield, as long as the * is first.

LIST lists the objects the shop keeper will sell you.
List <name> shows you only objects of that name.

SELL sells an object to a shop keeper.

VALUE asks the shop keeper how much he, she, or it will buy the item for.
 
  See also AUCTION, BANK, MONEY, SCORE.
~



0 CALENDAR FEASTDAYS~
CALENDAR

  The modern calendar is the Farede Callendar, which sets the first
year of the New Era after the War of the Hundred Years.

  The Farede Calendar has 10 days per week, 28 days per month, and
13 months per year.  These months are Taisham, Jumara, Saban, Aine,
Adar, Saven, Amadaine, Tammaz, Maigdhal, Choren, Shaldine, Nesan,
and Danu.

  Most people, however, reckon time by seasons and the dates of
feastdays.  Many such feastdays are not a part of any month.
These include Sunday, The Feast of Thanksgiving, and the Feast
of All Souls' Salvation (otherwise known as All Souls' Day).

  Feastdays are generally considered as a time of festivity and
celebration, as well as a day off from the toil of everyday life.
There are too many local feastdays to be listed here, but some of the
more widely celebrated and best-known can be found below:

The Feast of Lights-  This feast falls on the last day of Danu (the
   shortest day of the year) and the first day of Taisham.  In some
   places the second day of the festival (the first day of the year)
   is considered a good time to give charity.  In Cairhien, the Feast
   of Lights is a citywide party in which members of all walks of life
   join in drunken revelry and, yes, even orgies.

High Chasaline-  High Chasaline falls on the twelfth day of Taisham and
   is also known as "the Day of Reflection".  This is a day of dancing
   and reflection upon your good fortune, and complaining about
   anything is strictly frowned upon.

Chansein-  The third day of Jumara, Chansein is a day of indulgence
   in which people roam the streets handing out food to everyone they
   see... it is considered bad form to neglect to eat every bit of it.
   Chansein is celebrated throughout the Borderlands and in Arad Doman.

Feast of Abram-  The Feast of Abram falls on the ninth day of Jumara
   and is celebrated in Altara, Amadicia, Andor, Cairhien, Ghealdan,
   Illian, Murandy, Tarabon, and Tear.

Lamma Sor-  A day of remembrance for those who've fell defending the
   Borderlands, Lamma Sor is observed the day after the first quarter
   moon.  Nothing is eaten but bread, water, salt, and oil.  Lamma Sor
   is also known as the Day of Remembrance.

The Feast of Fools-  During the Feast of Fools, commoners assume the
   roles of their superiors, and their superiors carry out the tasks
   normally accomplished by their underlings.  The Feast is celebrated
   during Tammaz in Arad Doman and the Borderlands, and during Saven
   everywhere else.

Winternight-  Winternight is the night before Bel Tine, and is spent
   visiting friends and exchanging small gifts.

Bel Tine-  Celebrating the end of winter, Bel Tine is a celebration
   whose date is determined locally based upon the signs of a new
   spring.

Mabriam's Day-  On the eighteenth of Tammaz, nobody does any work,
   and it is common for young girls to play practical jokes on young
   men whom they favor... of course, if the young man happens to guess
   which girl pulled the prank on him, he gets a kiss from here as a
   reward.

Tandar-  Held on the ninth day of Maighdal, nobody is supposed to let
   the day end still holding a grudge against someone else.

Low Chasaline-  A day of fasting held on the eighteenth of Maighdal.

The Festival of Lanterns-  On the first day of Choren, brightly-
   colored paper lanterns are lit and hung everywhere.  The Festival
   is held throughout Arad Doman, Tarabon, Amadicia, Ghealdan, Altara,
   Murandy, and Illian.

Bel Arvina-  A feast held on the first day of autumn.

Amaetheon-  Held on the sixth day of Shaldine, Amaetheon is a feast
   held everywhere (except the Borderlands) in which the dead are
   remembered in a joyous celebration.

Shaoman-  On this twelfth day of Shaldine, children are praised and
   given gifts.  Going from house to house, small children sing songs
   and are rewarded with small gifts and treats.

Sunday-  A feastday and celebration held at midsummer.

  See also TIME, WEATHER.
~

