0 TREESINGING~
Syntax: treesing commands - lists the commands used in the treesinging editor.
Syntax: treesing show - lists the object's sung attributes.
Syntax: treesing name <name name2> - sets the object's keywords/identifiers.
Syntax: treesing type <treasure|furniture|armor|weapon> - choses object type.
Syntax: treesing short <description> - sets the object's inventory/short desc.
Syntax: treesing long <description> - sets the object's room/long desc.
Syntax: treesing form - when the object has been decided, the treesong begins.  Wait a few minutes for your work to be created!

Treesinging is the ability of gifted Ogier to infuse a certain life
within plants with their song, causing the plants to form in desired
formations.  These songs could also encourage a plant to grow stronger and
taller.  Objects created by the treesong cause no damage to the parent
plant, they are simply budded free.  

For an Ogier to use the Treesinging gift, it is required they reach a
certain maturity within the Wansho guild.  The Ogier must also be in a room
with the sector 'forest', 'field' or 'hills'.  
Those who create with the talent will have an easier time using the skill.
 
See also: OGIER, WANSHO, GUILD_WANSHO.
~

